    <directions>
      <step>  Mix fruit with 2 cups flour mixture. Heat oven to 275 degrees. line with
  wax paper and grease 6 loaf pans 8" x 4 1/2" X 2 1/2" deep. Beat butter and
  brown sugar until fluffy. Mix in egg yolks. Then mix in alternately just
  until smooth remaining flour mixture, juice and molasses. Turn into a large
  container and stir in fruit mix by hand. beat egg whites until soft peaks
  are formed and fold in to mixture.
  
  Bake for approximately 2 hours. yields 6 loaves Wrap well in foil. Can add
  brandy or rum at intervals.
  
  Decorations: Pineapple rings, maraschino cherries,pecans and or walnut
  halves marzipan, etc....
